  - {fileID: 6151968071869121696, guid: a29b1277854ae01418d0bc0f7dac7de2, type: 3}
  - {fileID: 4372608869806622657, guid: 436a08be908ef314b9ac11bdd6928532, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -5048871098781266669, guid: b51dd9f103733174d8c755350389ceb3, type: 3}
  - {fileID: -4572659564876447598, guid: 821caae4013a17740a8e06feea2dc085, type: 3}
  texts:
  - Dzan Dzydzba and his wife lie on the grass, watching clouds
  - "Suddenly, Delmachinczyk\u2019s army storms their town, burning and pillaging
    everything"
  - Dzan tries to defend his home but is defeated
  - "In a final act of cruelty, Delmachinczyk kills Dzan\u2019s wife"
  - "Grieving and powerless, Dzan swears vengeance \u2014 he will destroy Delmachinczyk\u2019s
    kingdom beyond Dragon Mountain"
  - After years of training
  - Dzan finds Delman attacking a village
  - Dzan fights bravely and saves the villagers, who gift him the Dragon Kimono,
    granting him new strength
  - "Following Delman\u2019s trail, Dzan confronts him on a bridge before Dragon
    Mountain. After a fierce duel, Delman escapes into his kingdom"
  - In the throne room, Dzan faces Delmachinczyk one last time. Desperate, Delmachinczyk
    consumes a cursed jar of margarine, gaining momentary power. But Dzan refuses
    to fall and defeats him
  - "Victorious, Dzan returns home, lying once more beneath the clouds \u2014 where
    he sees the image of his lost love"
  slideDurations:
  - 5
  - 5
  - 4
  - 4
  - 6
  - 3
  - 4
  - 7
  - 8
  - 10
  - 6
  barMoveDistance: 300
